<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tot-Killer's Mom Is Sentenced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	YORK, Va. (AP) -- A woman who slept off a night of partying while  
her 2 1/2-year-old daughter drowned her 10-month-old son in the 
bathtub was sentenced to seven years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Amy Barrett, 27, received the minimum sentence Wednesday, as  
recommended by a jury that convicted her of felony homicide and 
child neglect in February. A judge allowed her to remain free on 
$25,000 pending appeal. 
</P>
<P>
	According to testimony, Ms. Barrett's two children were in her  
boyfriend's care last April 17 when she came home around dawn from 
a night of partying and beer drinking. 
</P>
<P>
	When he went to work, she sent the girl to her room to play and  
put the baby on the floor nearby. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Barrett went to sleep on the sofa and didn't wake up until  
her boyfriend returned and found Joshua Barrett face down in water 
in the bathtub. Joshua was covered with a blanket, a laundry basket 
and toys that his sister had stacked upon him. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors never suggested that Ms. Barrett meant to harm her  
son, but said she knew the little girl was sometimes rough with the 
baby and put her social life ahead of her maternal 
responsibilities. 
</P>
<P>
	Defense attorneys had argued that the death was a tragic  
accident, not a crime. ``This is a strange and unique case'' to 
seek a homicide conviction for, attorney Michael Lee said. ``All 
she did was fall asleep.'' 
</P>
<P>
	She was convicted of felony homicide, a form of second-degree  
murder defined as accidentally killing someone during a felony. The 
felony, the jury decided, was child neglect. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Barrett's mother, Diana Barrett, has custody of the girl,  
now 3 1/2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
