<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> St. Francis, Pa. Hires New Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LORETTO, Pa. (AP) -- St. Francis College on Thursday hired Bobby  
Jones as men's basketball coach. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones, who was associate men's coach at Minnesota since 1997,  
replaces Tom McConnell, who resigned after a 9-17 season. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm looking forward to develop a long-term relationship with  
the college and the community and building a successful program,'' 
Jones said. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones coached for a Minnesota team that was 37-26 over two  
years, including a 20-15 mark in 1998 and a NIT championship. The 
Golden Gophers were 17-11 last season, losing in the first round of 
the NCAA tournament to Gonzaga after allegations surfaced that a 
tutor wrote papers for some members of the team. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones was listed among the top 10 recruiters in 1995-1996 by a  
basketball magazine, and was an assistant in 1994 to Pitt coach 
Ralph Willard. 
</P>
<P>
	``Coach Jones has the experience and credentials we need to  
develop a strong and successful program and to build upon a proud 
St. Francis College basketball tradition,'' said the Rev. Christian 
Oravec, president of the college. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones was an assistant at Western Kentucky from 1992-1994, where  
he also played for four years under current Minnesota coach Clem 
Haskins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
