<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Japan 3, United States 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BAUCHI, Nigeria (AP) -- Japan beat the United States 3-1 Thursday  
at the FIFA World Youth Championship, putting the Americans in 
danger of first-round elimination. 
</P>
<P>
	The Americans (1-1) are third in Group E with three points,  
trailing Cameroon (2-0) and behind Japan (1-1) on goal difference, 
with the Japanese plus-1 and the Americans minus-1. The top two 
teams in each of the six groups advance to the second round along 
with the four best third-place teams. 
</P>
<P>
	``Technically, the Japanese were a very good team and deserved  
the win today,'' U.S. coach Sigi Schmid said. ``We gave them too 
much space to work, and in this type of competition you cannot 
afford to give space. They did very well with their offensive 
chances.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The United States, which opened with a 1-0 win over England,  
plays Cameroon on Sunday at Bauchi in its final first-round game. 
Cameroon beat England 1-0 earlier Thursday in the under-20 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	With a win, the Americans would advance, and a tie would give  
them a chance depending on Sunday's other games. They also could 
advance with a loss, depending on other results. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm still very confident that we will advance,'' Schmid said.  
``Cameroon will be a very difficult opponent, but we know that our 
goals in this tournament ride on playing well on Sunday. We will be 
ready.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Japan, which lost to Cameroon 1-0 in its opener, went ahead of  
the Americans in the 12th minute when Nick Downing accidentally 
redirected a 25-yard drive into the penalty area past goalkeeper 
Nick Rimando into his own net. 
</P>
<P>
	Naohiro Takahara made it 2-0 seven minutes into the second half,  
but Ryan Futagaki, a fourth generation Japanese American, scored 
from 16 yards out off Shaun Tsakaris' corner kick in the 73rd 
minute, pulling the Americans within a goal. 
</P>
<P>
	Mitsuo Ogasawara got Japan's final goal with five minutes  
remaining. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
