<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bears Offer Center Wiegman $1.4M </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAKE FOREST, Ill. (AP) -- The Chicago Bears on Thursday decided  
to hold onto center Casey Wiegman, matching the Miami Dolphins' 
$1.4 million, two-year offer for the lineman. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bears had the right to match the Miami offer, which was made  
last week, and keep the 6-foot-3, 295-pounder. Wiegman started 15 
games last season. 
</P>
<P>
	Chicago claimed Wiegman off waivers from the New York Jets in  
1997 after he had spent time with the Jets and Indianapolis Colts. 
The former Iowa lineman missed much of the 1997 season due to a 
shoulder injury. 
</P>
</TEXT>
