<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stores To Accommodate Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Swifty Marts, a convenience store chain in the  
Southeast, agreed with the Justice Department on Thursday to modify 
all its 53 stores to accommodate customers with disabilities. 
</P>
<P>
	The out-of-court settlement resolves allegations that Suwannee  
Swifty Convenience Stores, located in Alabama, Florida and Georgia, 
violated the Americans With Disabilities Act by failing to provide 
refueling assistance or accessible parking and routes for disabled 
customers. 
</P>
<P>
	Under the agreement, Swifty Mart, based in Tallahassee, Fla.,  
will bring 16 of its stores into compliance by May of this year. By 
November 2000, the remaining 37 Swifty Mart stores will provide the 
same accessible features, the department said. 
</P>
<P>
	The stores were purchased in August 1997 by ES &AMP; ES Acquisitions  
Corp., which later formed Swifty Mart Corp. 
</P>
<P>
	``By removing barriers to accessibility at its stores, Swifty  
Mart Corp. is making it easier for more customers to conveniently 
shop in their community,'' said Bill Lann Lee, acting assistant 
attorney general for civil rights. ``Swifty Mart's cooperation 
throughout the investigation and willingness to improve compliance 
has led to a great result for people with disabilities and for the 
company.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Under the agreement, all Swifty Marts will provide:  
</P>
<P>
	--A universal accessible parking space or a van accessible  
parking space, reserved with a sign. 
</P>
<P>
	--Curb ramps where an accessible route crosses a curb.  
</P>
<P>
	--Refueling assistance to any disabled person who requests it,  
when more than one employee is on duty and safety concerns are not 
an issue. 
</P>
<P>
	--Training for its employees in the act's requirements.  
</P>
<P>
	Swifty Mart also agreed that buildings it purchases or leases in  
the future will meet ADA standards. The company also will pay a 
$5,000 civil penalty, the department said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
