<DOCNO> APW19990408.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-08 17:24:33 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Calif. Gov. Urges Public Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO (AP) -- Gov. Gray Davis wants to require community  
service as a condition of graduation for all students at state 
colleges and universities. 
</P>
<P>
	``One of the ethics of the World War II generation was a sense  
of obligation to the future, and an appreciation for what they 
inherited. That is getting away from us,'' Davis said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Some campuses already require community service as a condition  
of graduation. 
</P>
<P>
	Davis did not say how long students would be required to serve  
nor what kind of community service would be involved. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think its a good idea because I think a lot of the time at  
academic institutions we are separated from the community,'' said 
Natasha Clark, a social-work major at California State-Sacramento. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
