<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Duke's Brand Might Go Pro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Duke's Elton Brand has decided to skip his final two years of  
eligibility and will enter this year's NBA draft, CNN-Sports 
Illustrated reported Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Without citing any sources, CNN-SI said an official announcement  
will be made next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Duke sports information director Mike Cragg told The Associated  
Press that as far as he knows, Brand still hasn't made up his mind. 
</P>
<P>
	He also said that no announcement has been scheduled for next  
week. 
</P>
<P>
	The sophomore center has been honored this year by the AP, the  
Los Angeles Athletic Club, the Atlanta Tipoff Club, the United 
States Basketball Writers Association and the Atlantic Coast 
Conference. 
</P>
<P>
	Brand averaged 17.8 points and 9.8 rebounds for the Blue Devils,  
who finished 37-2, including a perfect record in ACC play. Duke 
lost to Connecticut, 77-74, in the NCAA championship game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
