<HEADLINE> Spiegel Recalls Baby Clothes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DOWNERS GROVE, Ill. (AP) -- Spiegel Catalog Inc. is recalling  
4,200 coveralls, sweaters and long-sleeve T-shirts because infants 
might be able to remove metal snaps and choke on them. 
</P>
<P>
	The company issued the recall Thursday after five customers  
returned garments from which the snaps had come off. No injuries 
have been reported. 
</P>
<P>
	All the garments are made with navy-colored stretch knit velvet  
material, and their collar tags read ``elements baby ... 
exclusively Spiegel.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The clothing was sold at Spiegel Ultimate Outlet stores and  
through Spiegel catalogs from November through February. The items 
can be returned to a Spiegel outlet for a refund. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	For more information, call Spiegel at (800) 443-4856 between 8  
a.m. and 7 p.m. EST Monday through Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
