<HEADLINE> Money Funds Rise in Latest Week / Money Market Funds  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Assets of the nation's retail money market  
mutual funds increased by $9.82 billion to $882.27 billion in the 
latest week, the Investment Company Institute said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Assets of taxable money market funds in the retail category  
increased by $7.10 billion to $727.30 billion for the week ended 
Wednesday, the Washington-based mutual fund trade group said. 
Tax-exempt fund assets increased by $2.72 billion to $154.97 
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Assets of institutional money market funds increased by $22.21  
billion to $593.47 billion for the same period. Among institutional 
funds, taxable money market fund assets increased by $20.03 billion 
to $542.92 billion while assets of tax-exempt funds increased by 
$2.18 billion to $50.55 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Total money market assets stood at $1.476 trillion for the week.  
</P>
<P>
	Assets for the previous week were revised to $1.444 trillion to  
reflect reporting errors and a change in the number of funds 
reporting. 
</P>
<P>
	The seven-day average yield on money market mutual funds rose to  
4.38 percent in the week ended Tuesday from 4.35 percent the 
previous week, said IBC's Money Fund Report, a trade journal 
published in Ashland, Mass., by IBC Financial Data Inc. The 30-day 
average yield rose to 4.35 percent from 4.34 percent, IBC Financial 
Data said. 
</P>
<P>
	The seven-day compounded yield rose to 4.48 percent from 4.44  
percent in the previous week, while the 30-day compounded yield 
rose to 4.45 percent from 4.44 percent, IBC Financial Data said. 
</P>
<P>
	The average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds slid  
to 59 days from 60 days the previous week, IBC Financial Data said. 
</P>
<P>
	The newsletter Bank Rate Monitor said its survey of 100 leading  
commercial banks, savings and loan associations and savings banks 
in the nation's 10 largest markets showed the annual percentage 
yield available on money market accounts held steady at 2.10 
percent as of Wednesday, compared with the previous week. 
</P>
<P>
	The North Palm Beach, Fla.-based newsletter said the annual  
percentage yield available on interest-bearing checking accounts 
remained unchanged at 0.95 percent from a week earlier. 
</P>
<P>
	Bank Rate Monitor said the annual percentage yield held steady  
at 4.14 percent on six-month certificates of deposit. Yields on 
1-year CDs fell to 4.37 percent from 4.38 percent but remained 
unchanged at 4.46 percent on 2 1/2-year CDs. Yields on 5-year CDs were 
unchanged at 4.61 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
