<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Cops Arrested in Conn. Crackdown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- Prosecutors have charged two Hartford  
police officers with coercing sexual favors from prostitutes under 
threat of arrest, and another officer and a former colleague 
pleaded guilty to related charges. 
</P>
<P>
	``These officers betrayed their trust, but more importantly they  
betrayed the other officers in the department,'' Michael Wolf, 
acting special agent in charge of the FBI's Connecticut office, 
said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Since October, a federal grand jury has been investigating  
alleged corruption in the department, including the prostitutes' 
allegations and the possibility that officers were involved in two 
unrelated, unsolved slayings. 
</P>
<P>
	Patrol officers Michael Basile, 41, and Jesus Rivera, 30, were  
charged with violating the civil rights of Hartford-area 
prostitutes. Both pleaded innocent Wednesday and were released on 
$100,000 bond. 
</P>
<P>
	Officer Salvatore Abateillo III, 35, pleaded guilty to aiding  
and abetting Rivera. He said he was present during alleged sexual 
acts but did not intervene. 
</P>
<P>
	Former Officer Jose L. Pizarro, 35, pleaded guilty to providing  
Rivera with a camera used to take nude pictures of the women. 
</P>
<P>
	All of the alleged crimes happened while the officers were in  
uniform and on duty, prosecutors said. Abateillo, Basile and Rivera 
were suspended without pay, police Chief Joseph F. Croughwell Jr. 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
