<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> H&AMP;R Block Discussing Acquisition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- H&AMP;R Block Inc. is negotiating to buy  
McGladrey &AMP; Pullen LLP, an acquisition that would make Block the 
sixth largest accounting firm in the country. 
</P>
<P>
	Both companies confirmed Thursday's report in The Wall Street  
Journal, which said Kansas City-based Block hopes to announce a 
deal by the end of the month. 
</P>
<P>
	While Block would not disclose any terms of the possible deal,  
the Journal said the price tag might be set at up to 25 percent 
above the value of McGladrey's annual revenues plus stock options. 
</P>
<P>
	McGladrey, based in Bloomington, Minn., had $296 million in  
revenues in its latest fiscal year, so the potential takeover could 
be valued at as much as $370 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal would be in line with recent industry trends in which  
publicly traded companies have been snapping up accounting firms. 
</P>
<P>
	Since January 1997, Century Business Services of Cleveland,  
American Express and H&AMP;R Block have bought about 80 privately held 
accounting firms. 
</P>
<P>
	If Block acquires McGladrey, it would vault the company ahead of  
both Century and American Express, said Arthur W. Bowman, editor of 
Bowman's Accounting Report, an Atlanta-based publication. 
</P>
<P>
	In recent years, Block has been pushing to transform itself from  
a traditional tax-preparation company into a one-stop financial 
advisory business. So far, Block has acquired two mortgage 
companies, a broker-dealer and five accounting firms. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
