<HEADLINE> 2 Octuplets Released From Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Two more of the surviving octuplets went home  
from the hospital Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Chidi, the second born, and Chima, the fourth born, left Texas  
Children's Hospital in Houston. The baby girls joined three of 
their siblings and their parents, Nkem Chukwu and Iyke Louis Udobi, 
at their home. 
</P>
<P>
	Chidi weighed just over 6 pounds, 3 ounces when she left the  
hospital, and Chima weighed just over 6 pounds, 13 ounces. Both 
girls weighed under 2 pounds at birth. 
</P>
<P>
	The two Chukwu babies remaining at Texas Children's Hospital --  
Gorom and Ikem -- were in serious condition Thursday night. Hospital 
spokeswoman Tina Foster said Gorom, the youngest of the infants, 
and Ikem, the firstborn boy, both have had successful abdominal 
surgery and are closer to going home. 
</P>
<P>
	The babies were born in December, but the weakest, a girl named  
Odera, died a week after birth. 
</P>
