<HEADLINE> Lockheed Martin Signs Launch Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BETHESDA, Md. (AP) -- Lockheed Martin Corp. said Thursday it will  
supply the Japanese Navy with eight more missile launch systems 
under a $70 million contract with Mitsubishi Heavy Industries. 
</P>
<P>
	Lockheed Martin has been supplying the MK 41 launch systems for  
Japanese destroyers since 1989. 
</P>
<P>
	The Japanese government decided last year to double the number  
of MK 41 launchers on its Muarasame-class ships from two to four. 
Each launcher can hold up to eight missiles. 
</P>
<P>
	Lockheed Martin, based in Bethesda, Md., is the largest defense  
contractor in the United States. 

</P>
</TEXT>
