<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sweden To Face Austria in Davis Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Reigning Davis Cup champion Sweden, bounced out of  
this year's play in the first round by Slovakia, will have to win a 
series in Austria to keep its place in the elite World Group. 
</P>
<P>
	The two countries were paired against each other Thursday in the  
draw for the World Group qualifying round to be played Sept. 24-26. 
Austria has home advantage. 
</P>
<P>
	The draw matched the eight losers from last weekend's World  
Group first-round ties against the winners from the second-tier 
zonal group. 
</P>
<P>
	The winners of September's matches will have berths in next  
year's World Group. Losers will go into the zonal divisions. 
</P>
<P>
	Sweden, the 1998 champion, was beaten at home by Slovakia 3-2  
last weekend in a major upset. It was the first time since 1991 
that Sweden had been knocked out in the first round. 
</P>
<P>
	Austria, playing without its top player, Thomas Muster, advanced  
to the qualifying round by downing Portugal 4-1 in a Euro-African 
zonal group match. 
</P>
<P>
	Britain, which lost to the United States 3-2 in a thrilling  
first-round competition was drawn against South Africa for the 
qualifying round. Britain will play at home. 
</P>
<P>
	Other World Group losers Germany, Spain, the Netherlands and the  
Czech Republic all will play away matches matches for September. 
</P>
<P>
	Germany will travel to Romania, Spain to New Zealand, the Czechs  
to Uzbekistan and the Dutch to Ecuador. 
</P>
<P>
	In other matches, Italy will host Finland and Zimbabwe is home  
against Chile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
