<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-08 15:44:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Seattle Activates Vin Baker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- Seattle SuperSonics forward Vin Baker, who has  
been sidelined for 10 games with a partial ligament tear of his 
right thumb, was activated Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Baker, a four-time All-Star, averaged 13.6 points and 6.1  
rebounds in 23 games before being placed on the injured list. 
</P>
<P>
	The Sonics placed reserve guard Drew Barry on the injured list,  
for pain in his back. 
</P>
</TEXT>
