<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Gets Life for Texas Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ABILENE, Texas (AP) -- A 23-year-old man accused of masterminding  
the murder-for-hire of a man for his gun collection has been 
convicted of capital murder and sentenced to life in prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Billy Don Wilson was convicted Thursday in last year's slaying  
of 46-year-old Mark Lund. The sentence was automatic because 
prosecutors did not seek the death penalty. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said the victim's son, 16-year-old Brandon Lund, sought  
to have his father killed. Wilson's group of rough loners was 
willing to commit the murder for the military gun collection valued 
at more than $5,000. 
</P>
<P>
	Brandon Lund changed his mind and tried to call off the hit, but  
Wilson and his gang refused. Dressed in black, they cut the phone 
line and crept through a window. After ransacking the house, Wilson 
pushed Lund onto a bed, shoved a pillow in his face and shot him in 
the head. 
</P>
<P>
	One of Wilson's gang scratched a cross on Brandon Lund's face  
with her fingernail and slashed him across the throat with a knife, 
according to the prosecution. 
</P>
<P>
	Defense attorney Mike Fouts argued that co-defendant Daniel  
Mullins was just as likely a triggerman as Wilson. Prosecutors said 
the evidence pointed to Wilson. 
</P>
<P>
	Trials are pending for four other members of the group. One  
suspect testified against Wilson and said in court that he expects 
to plead guilty to burglary later this month. 
</P>
<P>
	Brandon Lund, now 17, was charged with solicitation of capital  
murder. He was convicted in October and sentenced to two years in a 
juvenile prison. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear why Brandon wanted someone to kill his father. At  
his trial, prosecutor Dan Joiner argued that the teen-ager had no 
specific reason: ``He just didn't like the way his father was 
running the household.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
