<HEADLINE> DuPont Sues DCV in Patent Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) -- DuPont Co. has sued DCV Inc. and a  
subsidiary unit, Legacy USA Inc., charging they infringed on the 
chemical giant's trademark in promoting a product on the Internet, 
according to court papers filed in Delaware. 
</P>
<P>
	DCV Inc. was a biotechnology joint venture between DuPont and  
ConAgra Inc. from the mid-1980s until August 1997, when it was spun 
off. 
</P>
<P>
	DuPont is the only plaintiff to the lawsuit, filed in U.S.  
District Court in Wilmington on Wednesday. The company said it 
wants an injunction against DCV and Legacy to stop what it calls an 
infringement of the DuPont trademark and name. 

</P>
</TEXT>
