<HEADLINE> Southwest To Open Crew Base at BWI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Southwest Airlines will open a new flight  
attendant crew base in July at Baltimore/Washington International 
Airport as part of the carrier's eastward expansion. 
</P>
<P>
	The airline will locate 300 flight attendants at BWI as early as  
July and expects to add 500 more by the end of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	The new crew base will join current locations in Dallas,  
Houston, Phoenix, Chicago and Oakland, Calif. Systemwide, the 
carrier employs more than 5,250 flight attendants. 
</P>
<P>
	Southwest has been expanding its service toward the East Coast  
for several years. 
</P>
<P>
	The carrier added service in the New York area in March and will  
add service to Raleigh-Durham in North Carolina in June. In August, 
Southwest will add daily nonstop service to Las Vegas from 
Baltimore/Washington. 

</P>
