<HEADLINE> Pleasant Temper Wins Jenny Wiley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Pleasant Temper rallied from last to win  
the $113,300 Jenny Wiley Stakes at Keeneland on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Pleasant Temper, the 5-year-old daughter of Storm Cat, passed  
the leaders in the turn to take the lead with 3-16 of a mile to go 
and won by 1 1/2 lengths. 
</P>
<P>
	Pleasant Temper ran the distance in 1:40 4-5, one-fifth of a  
second slower than the stakes and course record. She returned 
$8.60, $4.20 and $3. 
</P>
<P>
	Mingling Glances was second and paid $5.80 and $3.60. Red Cat  
was third and returned $3.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Witchful Thinking, a 9-5 favorite, finished fourth.  
</P>
