<HEADLINE> Crew 2, Galaxy 1 (SO) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PASADENA, Calif. (AP) -- Stern John scored with 24 minutes to  
play and in the tie-breaking shootout as the Columbus Crew defeated 
the Los Angeles Galaxy 2-1 Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
	John evened the score in the 66th minute, with a left-footed  
shot from just inside the penalty area to slip the ball through the 
hands of Galaxy goalkeeper Kevin Hartman. The goal came three 
minutes after Hartman made a save on John's header. 
