<HEADLINE> Cable-Internet Deal Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	REDWOOD CITY, Calif. (AP) -- At Home Solutions today announced an  
agreement with cable operator Falcon Communications to deliver 
high-speed Internet services via cable lines to rural markets in 23 
states. 
</P>
<P>
	The service, to be named Falcon At Home, will have access to  
approximately 1.2 million homes and is expected to begin later this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	At Home Solutions is a joint venture between Redwood City-based  
At Home Network, Falcon Communications, 3Com Corp., Cisco Systems 
Inc. and Motorola Inc. The venture seeks to assist small- and 
medium-sized cable operators and systems in providing Internet 
services to their 15 million customers. 
</P>
<P>
	``Falcon is committed to delivering advanced communications  
services to the non-urban markets that form the core of our 
business,'' said Marc Nathanson, Falcon's chairman and chief 
executive officer. ``Every citizen in the United States, regardless 
of the size of community they live in, should have access to 
high-speed modems and services.'' 


</P>
</TEXT>
