<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Woman Dies in Bizarre Key Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- An elderly woman fell while she was trying to  
open her door with a key that was around her neck, strangling 
herself. 
</P>
<P>
	Beatrice Thornton, 73, apparently stumbled after she put the key  
in the lock on Wednesday at her fifth-floor apartment, Detective 
Dennis Logan said. 
</P>
<P>
	The key remained in the door lock, and her body weight held the  
strap tightly around her neck, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Her death appears to be the first of its kind. The Consumer  
Product Safety Commission has no reference in its files to adult 
deaths from key straps. 
</P>
<P>
	Two to three children die each year by strangling themselves,  
usually in cases in which a pacifier is tied around their necks by 
a cord, according to the commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
