<HEADLINE> Retail Sales at a Glance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	March sales and sales for the fiscal year to date reported by  
leading retailers. 
</P>
<P>
	The sales compare the current year's sales with those of the  
previous year. Retailers are ranked according to results at the end 
of March. 
</P>
<P>
	Reporting periods vary slightly. Most retailers' fiscal years  
end in late January or early February. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales include those from stores open at least a year, also known  
as same-store or comparable store sales, and total sales. Retailers 
release only percentage changes for same-store sales, while they 
provide dollar figures and percentages for total sales. 
</P>
<P>
	Securities analysts and investors believe same-store sales  
provide a more accurate assessment of a retailer's performance than 
total sales. 

</P>
<P>
 *Wal-Mart Stores Inc.  
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended April 2: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 11.3 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $13.89 billion, up 18.3 percent from $11.7  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Two months ended April 2: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 10.9 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $24.59 billion, up 18 percent from $20.84  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Sears, Roebuck and Co.	
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended April 3: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales up 2.1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $3.58 billion, down 2.9 percent from $3.69  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Two months ended April 3: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 1.6 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $6.24 billion, down 2.8 percent from $6.42  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Kmart Corp.	
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended March 31: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 8.1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $3.09 billion, up 10.1 percent from $2.81  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Two months ended March 31: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 7.1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $5.39 billion, up 8.9 percent from $4.95  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *J.C. Penney Co. Inc.	
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended April 3: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales fell 0.7 percent at Penney stores only.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $3.01 billion, up 9.7 percent from $2.74  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Two months ended April 3: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales fell 0.6 percent at Penney stores only.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $5.23 billion, up 7.7 percent from $4.85  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	(Total sales include J.C. Penney stores, its catalog and drug  
stores, including recently acquired drug chains.) 
</P>
<P>
 *Dayton Hudson Corp.	
