<HEADLINE> Dollar Falls, Gold Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar fell against most major currencies in  
European trading today. Gold prices were mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar fell to 120.64 Japanese yen from 121.36 yen late  
Wednesday, and was lower against the British pound and the euro, 
the currency of 11 European nations. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6078, up from $1.5954, while  
the euro rose to $1.0844 from $1.0795 late Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Other European dollar rates compared with late Wednesday  
included 1.4697 Swiss francs, down from 1.4781, and 1.4969 Canadian 
dollars, down from 1.5036. 
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar was worth 121.01 yen,  
1.4807 Swiss francs and 1.4978 Canadian dollars. The British pound 
was worth $1.6070 and the euro was quoted at $1.0788. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 1.8036 German marks, down from 1.8118; 
6.0490 French francs, down from 6.0765; and 1,785.57 Italian lire, 
down from 1,793.67. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $279.80 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$280.10 on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $280.65, up from $280.10.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold rose $0.20 in Hong Kong to close at $280.65.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $4.91 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$4.97. 
</P>
</TEXT>
