<HEADLINE> Del. House Explosion Kills One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DOVER, Del. (AP) -- A blast possibly caused by a propane tank  
leveled a house early today, killing the occupant and injuring 
three neighbors who were hit by flying glass. 
</P>
<P>
	All that remained of the two-story house was the foundation,  
police said. The blast in the Royal Grant neighborhood near Dover 
was heard as far as three miles away, at Dover Air Force Base, and 
spread debris over an area 50 feet wide and 100 feet long. 
</P>
<P>
	Terry L. Midcap, 52, was killed in the 3 a.m. blast, state  
police Cpl. Alice Bailey said. Midcap's wife and teen-age daughter 
were not at home. 
</P>
<P>
	Flying glass hit three neighbors, who were taken to Kent General  
Hospital. They were expected to be treated and released. 
</P>
<P>
	The state fire marshal's office was investigating the blast with  
the help of state police and the federal Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco 
and Firearms. Investigators believe the blast may have been caused 
by a propane tank outside Midcap's home, Ms. Bailey said. 
</P>
<P>
	Police blocked off the area and remained on the scene several  
hours after the explosion, but neighbors were not immediately 
evacuated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
