<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dolphins Sign Vikings' Goodwin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DAVIE, Fla. (AP) -- The Miami Dolphins signed Minnesota tight end  
Hunter Goodwin to an offer sheet Thursday, the team's second 
pursuit of a restricted free agent in less than a week. 
</P>
<P>
	Later Thursday, Miami lost a bid for center Casey Wiegmann when  
Chicago matched the Dolphins' offer of $1.4 million over two years. 
</P>
<P>
	The Vikings have seven days to match Goodwin's three-year deal.  
Financial terms were not disclosed, though reports said the deal 
was worth $2.5 million, including a $750,000 signing bonus. 
</P>
<P>
	If the Vikings do not match the offer, they will receive Miami's  
fourth-round draft pick as compensation. Goodwin was Minnesota's 
fourth-round selection in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	Goodwin, 26, played 15 games for the Vikings last season as a  
backup to Andrew Glover. He caught three passes for 16 yards and is 
better known for his blocking. In three seasons, he has 11 catches 
for 101 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dolphins also re-signed linebacker Anthony Harris to a  
two-year contract Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Harris, 26, played only five games last season after spraining  
his left knee in training camp and losing his starting spot to 
Robert Jones. He recorded no tackles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
