<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-08 12:45:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> BMW To Make Cars at Russian Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- BMW plans to make limousines and off-road vehicles  
at a Russian factory in the republic of Kaliningrad, the German 
automaker said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The first cars are expected to roll off the assembly line this  
summer from the Avtotor plant, said Lueder Paysen, head of BWM's 
executive sales division. 
</P>
<P>
	``We believe that Russia will sooner or later become a big  
market,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Thursday's announcement came the same day that the Russian  
government sought to assure Western businesses that Moscow's 
protests against NATO raids on Yugoslavia wouldn't hurt their 
operations in Russia. 
</P>
<P>
	The Avtotor plant will have an annual production capacity of  
10,000 units, but no date has been set for reaching this target. 
</P>
<P>
	Kaliningrad is a Russian enclave on the Baltic Sea between  
Lithuania and Poland. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to limousines, the plant will make Land Rover  
Defenders, an off-road vehicle in production since 1948. 
</P>
<P>
	BMW plans to adapt its Russian-made models to rough local road  
conditions. ``The cars' chassis will be higher and suspension will 
be sturdier than in the models made in Germany,'' Paysen said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
